The paper deals with learning a linear subspace from data corrupted by outliers, which is a problem in machine learning and computer vision. The paper proposes a new method called Dual Principal Component Pursuit (DPCP) and provides a refined geometric analysis and a new statistical analysis. These topics are closely related to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), information theory (cs.IT), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
